data.enText: a situation in which a comment, an instruction, etc. is not understood correctly

data.chText: 一定是搞错了——我以为我订的是更小型号的。
data.enText: There must be some misunderstanding─I thought I ordered the smaller model.

data.chText: 对于这项工作的真实目的，仍然存在着严重的误解。
data.enText: There is still a fundamental misunderstanding about the real purpose of this work.

data.chText: 所有的合同都经过翻译，以避免公司间发生任何误解。
data.enText: All contracts are translated to avoid any misunderstanding between the companies.

data.chText: 我们对这个提案的看法有点分歧。
data.enText: We had a little misunderstanding over the bill.

tr: an understanding of something that is not correct
example: he wasn't going to admit his mistake
make no mistake about his intentions
there must be some misunderstanding--I don't have a sister
his misinterpretation of the question caused his error
there was no mistaking her meaning

value.def: A misunderstanding is a failure to understand something properly, for example a situation or a person's remarks.

example.ex: There has been some misunderstanding of our publishing aims...
example.tran: 关于我们的出版目的存在着某些误解。

example.ex: Tell your midwife what you want so she can make a note of it and avoid misunderstandings.
example.tran: 把你的要求告诉助产士，这样她可以记下来，避免产生误解。

value.def: You can refer to a disagreement or slight quarrel as a misunderstanding .
